# 🚀 🧠 FULL PROJECT EXPLANATION (DETAILED)

---

# 🟡 1. PROJECT OVERVIEW

👉 I developed a **Full Stack Notes Application**

📌 Purpose:

* To create, edit, and manage notes digitally
* Provide rich text editing
* Run as both **web app + desktop app**

---

# 🟡 2. FRONTEND (UI PART)

## 🔹 Technologies Used:

* **HTML**
* **Tailwind CSS**
* **JavaScript**
* **Thymeleaf (for dynamic data rendering)**

---

## 🔹 UI FEATURES

✔ Clean modern UI (inspired by Google Keep)
✔ Fully responsive (mobile + laptop)
✔ Navbar + Search
✔ Notes grid layout
✔ Floating/Add button

---

## 🔹 USER ACTIONS

👉 User can:

* Create note
* Edit note
* Archive note
* Delete note
* Restore note

---

## 🔹 HOW UI WORKS

👉 Example:

1. User clicks **➕ Add**
2. Opens editor page
3. Writes note
4. Clicks Save
5. Note appears on homepage

---

# 🟡 3. RICH TEXT EDITOR

## 🔹 Tool Used:

👉 **Quill.js**

---

## 🔹 FEATURES

✔ Bold / Italic / Underline
✔ Text alignment
✔ Lists
✔ Links
✔ Images
✔ Styled content

---

## 🔹 IMPORTANT POINT

👉 Data is stored as **HTML format**

Example:

```html
<b>Hello</b> <i>World</i>
```

---

# 🟡 4. BACKEND (LOGIC PART)

## 🔹 Technology:

👉 **Java Spring Boot**

---

## 🔹 ARCHITECTURE

```plaintext
Controller → Service → Repository → Database
```

---

## 🔹 COMPONENTS

### 1. Controller

👉 Handles HTTP requests

```java
@GetMapping("/")
@PostMapping("/save")
```

---

### 2. Service

👉 Business logic

```java
repo.save(note);
```

---

### 3. Repository

👉 Database interaction (JPA)

```java
extends JpaRepository
```

---

# 🟡 5. DATABASE (VERY IMPORTANT)

## 🔹 Used:

👉 **H2 Database (In-Memory)**

---

## 🔹 WHY H2?

✔ Easy to use
✔ No installation needed
✔ Fast
✔ Good for projects

---

## 🔹 KEY POINT (VERY IMPORTANT)

👉 Data is **TEMPORARY**

```plaintext
When server stops → ALL DATA DELETED ❗
```

---

## 🔹 CONFIGURATION

```properties
spring.datasource.url=jdbc:h2:mem:testdb
spring.jpa.hibernate.ddl-auto=update
```

---

## 🔹 WHAT IS STORED

* Title
* Content (HTML)
* Date & time
* Archive status
* Delete status

---

# 🟡 6. FLOW OF DATA (WEB APP)

```plaintext
User Action
   ↓
Frontend (HTML + JS)
   ↓
Controller (Spring Boot)
   ↓
Service Layer
   ↓
Repository (JPA)
   ↓
H2 Database
   ↓
Response back to UI
```

---

# 🟡 7. CRUD OPERATIONS

✔ Create → Save note
✔ Read → Display notes
✔ Update → Edit note
✔ Delete → Move to bin

